And...

253
00:21:54,330 --> 00:21:56,040
I'm bummed.

254
00:21:56,840 --> 00:22:03,580
Everyone worked
so hard at it.

255
00:22:15,490 --> 00:22:17,504
Ten million yen.

256
00:22:17,504 --> 00:22:20,290
The loan is for
ten million yen?

257
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:26,000
There's nothing
you can do about it.

258
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:30,370
It's not something you
should get involved in.

259
00:22:30,370 --> 00:22:32,170
But...

260
00:22:32,840 --> 00:22:35,510
If that pub closes down...

261
00:22:35,510 --> 00:22:37,776
Koba-san will lose his dream.

262
00:22:37,776 --> 00:22:41,330
It's not your duty
to look after his life.

263
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:45,250
He danced in front
of his daughter recently.

264
00:22:46,790 --> 00:22:50,120
<i>When I saw him dancing
passionately for his daughter...</i>

265
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:54,160
I wanted him to rise
victorious in life.

266
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:02,970
Rise victorious in life?

267
00:23:04,110 --> 00:23:07,910
After working for you as
an investigator, I realized

268
00:23:07,910 --> 00:23:11,540
that you have to win in
court or it means nothing.

269
00:23:11,540 --> 00:23:14,170
If you don't win, then
you will end up a loser.

270
00:23:14,170 --> 00:23:16,790
So to win, I did anything
and everything.

271
00:23:16,790 --> 00:23:18,850
Even sleazy things.

272
00:23:22,230 --> 00:23:26,400
Sotokoba should
live his own life.

273
00:23:28,270 --> 00:23:31,370
You have to live
for Marimo-chan.

274
00:23:38,210 --> 00:23:43,210
I can't ignore my
friend in distress.

275
00:23:59,030 --> 00:24:00,960
Where is it?

276
00:24:11,070 --> 00:24:13,240
<i>Are you after her fortune?</i>

277
00:24:18,050 --> 00:24:21,340
So he was fooling around
with a woman in this room.

278
00:24:21,340 --> 00:24:24,420
Do I have to keep a
constant eye on him?

279
00:24:27,860 --> 00:24:29,690
What are you doing here?

280
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:34,270
He's not home.

281
00:24:34,270 --> 00:24:36,700
Didn't second
semester start?

282
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:41,100
What are you going to do?
Go to college or go to work?

283
00:24:41,610 --> 00:24:44,100
Did you come
here for me?

284
00:24:44,100 --> 00:24:46,940
Of course. I'm worried.

285
00:24:48,510 --> 00:24:51,250
I haven't decided yet.

286
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:53,620
Why?

287
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:59,260
Before summer, I was
determined to go to college.

288
00:24:59,790 --> 00:25:02,290
But now, I'm wondering if
there's any meaning to going

289
00:25:02,290 --> 00:25:04,890
to college when I don't
know what I want out of life.

290
00:25:05,930 --> 00:25:08,760
That's what I learned
from working there.

291
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:12,750
Everyone has a dream... and
is striving hard towards it.

292
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:16,940
That made me want to be
engrossed in something, too.

293
00:25:21,010 --> 00:25:23,010
What do you want to do?

294
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:26,480
I don't know yet.

295
00:25:28,020 --> 00:25:30,750
That sounds deep.

296
00:25:32,090 --> 00:25:35,360
I met a lot of strange
people this summer.

297
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:39,260
That sounds nice.

298
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:44,570
You're great.

299
00:25:55,210 --> 00:25:57,850
I feel like hugging
you tightly.

300
00:26:02,790 --> 00:26:04,720
Shinpei-chan!

301
00:26:06,090 --> 00:26:08,290
What were you doing?
What were you trying to do?

302
00:26:08,290 --> 00:26:11,390
- Did you drag in a guy?
- It's not what you think!

303
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:18,330
What are you doing
behind her father's back!?

304
00:26:19,340 --> 00:26:23,810
- Why are you here?
- I'm going to get fired.

305
00:26:23,810 --> 00:26:26,980
My superior thinks I'm
working on the side.

306
00:26:26,980 --> 00:26:28,910
Remember the time
I danced at the pub?

307
00:26:28,910 --> 00:26:31,880
A civilian who saw that
reported it to my superior.

308
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:35,150
I said I wasn't working there,
but they wouldn't believe me.

309
00:26:35,150 --> 00:26:38,760
I have absolutely no
interest in dancing!

310
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:41,060
What do you mean?
You were really into it.

311
00:26:43,430 --> 00:26:44,890
A big job?

312
00:26:46,060 --> 00:26:49,910
- Are you out of money?
- That's right.

313
00:26:49,910 --> 00:26:52,570
You're the only one
that I can turn to.

314
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:56,270
Refer me to someone who
will pay me ten million yen.

315
00:26:56,940 --> 00:26:58,740
Ten million yen?

316
00:26:59,540 --> 00:27:03,450
You have the right
contacts, don't you?

317
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:08,500
- Will this guy do?
- Yes, he'll do.

318
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:14,000
Can we trust this
bearded guy to do it?

319
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:16,700
There's no one else!

320
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:22,900
If we succeed, we can
live it up in Thailand!

321
00:27:30,910 --> 00:27:34,110
They want you to steal
Hokuto Kôsan's microchip.

322
00:27:34,940 --> 00:27:38,810
- Am I going to be a thief?
- An industry spy.

323
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:46,960
They'll pay you five
million yen upfront,

324
00:27:46,960 --> 00:27:49,190
and the rest when
the job is done.

325
00:27:51,760 --> 00:27:53,900
If you tell anyone,
we'll kill you.

326
00:28:19,620 --> 00:28:21,830
Will you hear me out?
I don't know what to do.

327
00:28:21,830 --> 00:28:24,260
Sorry, but I'm going
to be busy from now.

328
00:28:24,260 --> 00:28:26,130
Where's the flashlight?

329
00:28:28,700 --> 00:28:30,630
Do you know where
the flashlight is?

330
00:28:34,140 --> 00:28:36,040
Did you touch this?

331
00:28:37,270 --> 00:28:39,140
What were you
going to do with Mama's

332
00:28:39,140 --> 00:28:41,040
insurance proceeds?

333
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:44,480
Well...

334
00:28:45,550 --> 00:28:48,250
What's the big deal?
I only touched it.

335
00:28:49,050 --> 00:28:50,850
You can use it.

336
00:28:52,290 --> 00:28:54,690
If you really need the
money, you can use it.

337
00:28:56,230 --> 00:28:59,330
But I want to know what
you're going to use it for.

338
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:03,830
I want to know. Aren't
we father and daughter?

339
00:29:09,670 --> 00:29:12,340
Well, it's for...

340
00:29:12,980 --> 00:29:15,110
Asami-chan,
what are you doing?

341
00:29:16,610 --> 00:29:19,320
<i>If that pub closes down...</i>

342
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:22,020
<i>Koba-san will lose his dream.</i>

343
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:25,050
Marimo-chan, we're
about to open shortly.

344
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:29,530
Why do I have
to tell you?

345
00:29:29,530 --> 00:29:31,190
I want to know.

346
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:35,430
- I just need the money!
- That doesn't tell me anything!

347
00:29:35,770 --> 00:29:39,140
It's for our living expenses.

348
00:29:39,140 --> 00:29:41,600
That's being cowardly
as a parent.

349
00:29:41,600 --> 00:29:44,010
Stay out of this.

350
00:29:44,010 --> 00:29:46,710
I don't need to give a reason
to use my child's money.

351
00:29:46,710 --> 00:29:49,340
Will you hand over those
insurance proceeds?

352
00:29:49,650 --> 00:29:51,780
You said I could use it.

353
00:29:51,780 --> 00:29:53,680
Will you lend it to me?

354
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:56,190
Why won't you tell
me the truth?

355
00:29:57,790 --> 00:30:02,460
Stop acting big in front
of me as a father.

356
00:30:03,690 --> 00:30:07,500
You don't show me
your true feelings.

357
00:30:11,270 --> 00:30:13,300
I can't be a real
family with you.

358
00:30:16,070 --> 00:30:18,270
Marimo-chan,
you've got it wrong.

359
00:30:19,780 --> 00:30:22,780
He went to the ward
office today to register you

360
00:30:22,780 --> 00:30:25,050
as his own daughter.

361
00:30:25,050 --> 00:30:26,650
Don't say
unnecessary things.

362
00:30:26,650 --> 00:30:28,350
Register me?

363
00:30:29,050 --> 00:30:33,060
Don't act on
your own like that.

364
00:30:33,620 --> 00:30:35,890
What's with you?

365
00:30:35,890 --> 00:30:39,400
Don't decide such
important things on your own!

366
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:41,730
I am not one of your belongings!

367
00:30:43,100 --> 00:30:46,270
I hate you.

368
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:50,240
Go ahead and use it,
if you want.

369
00:30:58,780 --> 00:31:01,450
How lucky for me!

370
00:31:03,420 --> 00:31:05,690
Shinpei, you're the worst.

371
00:31:06,660 --> 00:31:09,090
If you use that money, you
will become a rotten person.

372
00:31:09,090 --> 00:31:10,830
Shinpei?

373
00:31:15,060 --> 00:31:17,200
I know that.

374
00:31:24,070 --> 00:31:27,440
Shinpei! What
happened? Tell me!

375
00:31:54,170 --> 00:31:56,740
He's like a child.

376
00:32:05,310 --> 00:32:06,880
Konari-san.

377
00:32:08,380 --> 00:32:09,990
Where's Shinpei?

378
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:12,120
He went out.

379
00:32:28,540 --> 00:32:31,070
Will you give this to him?

380
00:32:31,810 --> 00:32:33,580
What is it for?

381
00:32:36,350 --> 00:32:43,020
It's the money
for your dream.

382
00:32:55,670 --> 00:32:59,400
Shinpei, I turned that deal
down and returned the money.

383
00:33:01,300 --> 00:33:04,970
It sounds too dangerous,
no matter how I look at it.

384
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:08,610
Where's Shinpei?

385
00:33:12,320 --> 00:33:15,150
Oh, no! What am
I going to do?

386
00:33:15,150 --> 00:33:19,490
- Did Shinpei go? Stop him!
- What's going on?

387
00:33:22,490 --> 00:33:25,330
Tell me what's going on.
Where did Shinpei go?

388
00:33:32,670 --> 00:33:34,170
<i>See you!</i>

389
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:39,740
<i>I hate you.</i>

390
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:55,490
<i>Well, it's for...</i>

391
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:11,370
If you don't talk to me,
how am I supposed to know!

392
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:51,110
Marimo-chan...

393
00:34:54,250 --> 00:34:56,620
Shinpei is...

394
00:35:18,900 --> 00:35:22,740
- What is his condition?
- We're still treating him.

395
00:35:25,940 --> 00:35:28,910
What's going on?

396
00:35:31,180 --> 00:35:34,050
I just came from the site!
His motorcycle was totaled.

397
00:35:34,690 --> 00:35:37,390
There's no way he
can survive that!

398
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:40,690
It's my fault.

399
00:35:41,060 --> 00:35:44,960
No, it's not. It's my fault.

400
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:48,270
Will you be quiet?
We're in a hospital.

401
00:35:51,540 --> 00:35:53,140
His pulse isn't coming back.

402
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:57,570
I'm a doctor. Please let
me go inside and watch.

403
00:36:02,050 --> 00:36:06,360
Please put this
somewhere on his body.

404
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:08,550
Please save him.

405
00:36:10,650 --> 00:36:12,460
I'll hold on to it.

406
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:27,630
<i>My daughter?
Are you serious?</i>

407
00:36:27,630 --> 00:36:29,110
<i>That's a harsh joke!</i>

408
00:36:29,110 --> 00:36:31,880
<i>- Are you going to take it?
- You told me to take it.</i>

409
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:34,510
<i>- That's my entire fortune!
- You told me to take it.</i>

410
00:36:34,510 --> 00:36:37,250
<i>Don't do to others what you
don't want done to you. Stupid.</i>

411
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,820
<i>Will you lock the door!</i>

412
00:36:45,100 --> 00:36:55,130
<i>Marimo, you were
conceived with all of our love.</i>

413
00:36:58,440 --> 00:37:01,200
<i>Please believe me.
I really didn't do it.</i>

414
00:37:01,940 --> 00:37:03,640
<i>I can swear to you!</i>

415
00:37:06,210 --> 00:37:08,480
<i>Why did you
hurt my Marimo!?</i>

416
00:37:09,010 --> 00:37:11,030
<i>It'll heal right away.</i>

417
00:37:11,030 --> 00:37:13,870
<i>One gets irate
when one is hungry.</i>

418
00:37:13,870 --> 00:37:16,020
<i>Don't hold back and eat.</i>

419
00:37:18,060 --> 00:37:21,930
Take me to
someplace fancier.

420
00:37:34,910 --> 00:37:36,870
How old do you
think you are?

421
00:37:46,750 --> 00:37:49,720
<i>What's so good about
an ordinary life?</i>

422
00:37:50,750 --> 00:37:52,960
<i>It's rough being a parent.</i>

423
00:37:54,590 --> 00:37:56,360
Be my parent.

424
00:38:18,620 --> 00:38:20,550
Don't leave me alone.

425
00:38:24,390 --> 00:38:27,760
Don't leave me alone!
Don't die!

426
00:38:28,630 --> 00:38:32,030
I don't want to be alone!

427
00:38:34,230 --> 00:38:36,500
After Mama died...

428
00:38:36,500 --> 00:38:39,070
All my relatives rejected me.

429
00:38:39,670 --> 00:38:42,110
<i>But you took me in.</i>

430
00:38:42,110 --> 00:38:45,080
That made me happy...
very happy!

431
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:50,180
I felt I wasn't alone anymore.

432
00:38:50,180 --> 00:38:53,120
That feeling made me
very happy.

433
00:38:54,850 --> 00:38:57,290
I've been enjoying it lately.

434
00:38:57,290 --> 00:39:00,160
<i>I've been enjoying
spending time with you.</i>

435
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:03,760
So I don't want to be
alone anymore!

436
00:39:06,460 --> 00:39:10,430
Live... for me!

437
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:18,980
I have a lot to apologize
to you about.

438
00:39:21,350 --> 00:39:24,050
I haven't called you "papa" yet.

439
00:39:24,950 --> 00:39:28,950
So please...

440
00:39:34,690 --> 00:39:37,990
Shinpei, come back.

441
00:39:40,260 --> 00:39:42,230
Shinpei!

442
00:39:44,130 --> 00:39:47,970
Shinpei!

443
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:17,500
WE'RE HAVING A FAREWELL
AND SEND-OFF PARTY TODAY

444
00:40:18,470 --> 00:40:21,140
Thank you for coming
when you're busy.

445
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:29,450
- Satoi-san.
- Why did Shinpei...

446
00:40:45,830 --> 00:40:48,490
Satoi, what're you
doing here?

447
00:40:48,490 --> 00:40:52,540
When I think about Marimo-chan,
who is left all alone...

448
00:40:53,070 --> 00:40:56,730
I don't know what to say.
Hey, Shinpei is here.

449
00:40:56,730 --> 00:40:59,510
Yes, he's here. He was
discharged today.

450
00:40:59,510 --> 00:41:02,980
Discharged? What is
this send-off party for?

451
00:41:02,980 --> 00:41:05,410
Aren't they overdoing it?

452
00:41:05,410 --> 00:41:07,720
They should be celebrating
my hospital discharge.

453
00:41:09,290 --> 00:41:13,190
- Hey!
- It's the loser!

454
00:41:13,190 --> 00:41:16,460
What's going on?
I thought you died.

455
00:41:16,460 --> 00:41:19,200
Why are you alive?
Why am I here?

456
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:21,360
I'm immortal.

457
00:41:22,170 --> 00:41:23,970
Stop joking around.

458
00:41:23,970 --> 00:41:27,900
Satoi, I got to see you again!
That makes me so happy!

459
00:41:28,210 --> 00:41:30,470
Congratulations on your
hospital discharge.

460
00:41:30,470 --> 00:41:34,410
How considerate of you!
A onsen trip for two!

461
00:41:34,410 --> 00:41:36,180
Isn't this the one
I bought before?

462
00:41:36,180 --> 00:41:37,750
Go with Asami-san.

463
00:41:38,280 --> 00:41:42,150
- What a kid.
- I feel bad.

464
00:41:42,950 --> 00:41:45,800
So you've grown up.

465
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:48,120
Don't you have something
else to say to him?

466
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:50,840
Remember what
you said that day?

467
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:54,470
- Forget that.
- What is it?

468
00:41:54,470 --> 00:41:56,370
- Go ahead and say it.
- Come out with it.

469
00:41:56,370 --> 00:42:00,870
- Now is your chance.
- What is it? Tell me.

470
00:42:04,640 --> 00:42:07,310
Are you all having
nice dreams?

471
00:42:10,280 --> 00:42:12,680
This is a send-off party
for the four who will be

472
00:42:12,680 --> 00:42:14,520
turning their dreams
into reality.

473
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:18,970
But this won't be farewell.
This is just their departure!

474
00:42:18,970 --> 00:42:22,790
And this will be their last
stage performance here!

475
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:29,530
Dreams are there
to be realized.

476
00:42:30,870 --> 00:42:33,540
Let's dance till we drop!

477
00:42:51,660 --> 00:42:53,820
Congratulations on your
hospital discharge, Papa.

478
00:42:54,860 --> 00:42:56,960
So you said it.

479
00:42:58,730 --> 00:43:01,200
I didn't hear it too well.
Can you say it again?

480
00:43:01,200 --> 00:43:02,400
No.

481
00:43:43,840 --> 00:43:46,110
I found a dream.

482
00:43:47,380 --> 00:43:50,650
I'm going to be a nurse,
just like my mama.

483
00:43:51,850 --> 00:43:54,350
Come and work for me then.

484
00:44:37,400 --> 00:44:39,900
HAKUAI NURSING SCHOOL

485
00:44:41,770 --> 00:44:44,000
<i>I found a dream for myself.</i>

486
00:44:45,300 --> 00:44:48,170
<i>I am leaving this place today.</i>

487
00:44:53,540 --> 00:44:56,050
Are you going to be
lonely without me?

488
00:44:57,210 --> 00:44:59,280
It'll be a big relief.

489
00:45:00,720 --> 00:45:02,590
Likewise.

490
00:45:03,290 --> 00:45:07,600
Can a spoiled brat like
you survive in a dorm?

491
00:45:07,600 --> 00:45:09,390
Oh, be quiet.

492
00:45:09,390 --> 00:45:14,060
You can still
change your mind.

493
00:45:15,900 --> 00:45:20,370
I'll make my
dream come true.

494
00:45:26,840 --> 00:45:29,280
Thanks for all
you've done.

495
00:45:32,650 --> 00:45:34,420
See you.

496
00:45:44,100 --> 00:45:47,100
<i>My summer is about
to come an end.</i>

497
00:45:47,400 --> 00:45:51,000
<i>With all that's happened,
I had the best summer ever.</i>

498
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:57,500
<i>That's because
I met you, Papa.</i>

499
00:46:31,000 --> 00:46:33,000
2014-11

